1. g3 Nf6 2. Bg2 d5 3. Nf3 Bf5 4. c4 c6 5. cxd5 cxd5 6. Qb3 Qb6 7. Qxb6 axb6 8. Nc3 e6 9. O-O Bc5 10. d3 Nc6 11. Bd2 O-O 12. a3 Nd4 13. Nxd4 Bxd4 14. Rab1! { [%cal Gc3b5] } 14... Bxc3 15. Bxc3 { White has the two bishops, better structure, and has the long term plan of expanding on the kingside and playing f5. } { [%csl Gc3,Gg2] } 15... Nd7 16. h3! Bg6 17. f4! { [%csl Rg6] } 17... Nc5 { [%csl Ge5][%cal Gc3e5] } 18. g4! { [%cal Gc3g7] } 18... Rfd8 19. b4 Nd7 20. Bb2 Rac8 21. Rbc1 f6 22. f5! { Black's structure completely crumbles after this. } 22... Bf7 23. fxe6 Bxe6 { [%csl Rb7,Rb6,Rd5,Gb2,Gg2] } 24. Rxc8 Rxc8 25. Rc1 Rxc1+ 26. Bxc1 { [%cal Gg1d4] } 26... Ne5 27. Kf2 Kf7 28. Bb2 Ke7 29. g5! { White inflicts more structural damage. } 29... Kd6 30. gxf6 gxf6 { [%csl Rb7,Rb6,Rd5,Rf6,Rh7] } 31. Bd4 Nd7 32. Kg3 Kc6 33. a4 b5 34. a5 { [%csl Ga5] } 34... Kd6 35. Kf4 Bf7 36. Bf3 Be6 37. h4 Bh3 38. Bh5 Be6 39. Be8 Bh3 40. Bf7 Bf1 41. Bh5 Bh3 42. Bf3 Be6 43. e4 Bf7 44. Bxf6! { With all of Black's pawns weak and frozen on light squares, White simplifies to a winning same-colored bishop ending. } 44... Nxf6 45. e5+ Ke6 46. exf6 Kxf6 47. d4! { [%csl Gf3,Rf7,Yb7,Yb5,Yd5,Yh7] } 47... Be6 48. Be2 Bd7 49. Bd3 h6 50. Be2 Bh3 51. Bxb5 Ke6 52. Be2 Kd6 53. b5 Bd7 54. Bd3 Bh3 55. a6 bxa6 56. bxa6 Bd7 57. Bf5 Bb5 58. Bc8 Kc7 59. Bb7 Kb6 60. Ke5 Bc4 61. Kf6 Bd3 62. Kg7 h5 63. Kh6 Be2 64. Bxd5 Kxa6 65. Bf7 Kb5 66. Bxh5 Bd3 67. Bf7 1-0


